## Reflection — Day 4 Session 1

- for loops repeat through a known collection or range
- while loops repeat until a condition becomes False
- Conditionals inside loops make each repetition intelligent
- Accumulator variables collect results across all repetitions
- break stops a loop early when a condition is met
- continue skips one item and moves to the next
- Loops are essential for processing datasets automatically

  
## Reflection — Day 4 Session 2

- enumerate() gives both index and value in a loop
- Nested lists can be unpacked directly in a for loop
- Accumulator variables track running totals and counts
- Lists like rare_species and alert_sites collect flagged items
- Loops replace hundreds of manual checks with a few lines
- Combining loops, conditionals and variables solves real problems
- Formatting output with :> and :< aligns columns cleanly
